Package odysseus.common.entities

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbsLevel
    A level is composed of a board, bullpen with pieces, and an objective for play.
    Board
    The board is a collection of squares that constitute playable and nonplayable area.
    Bullpen
    The Bullpen stores the pieces for a level.
    Counter
    Keeps track of how many moves the player has made.
    GameTimer
    A timer to be used to keep track of game time in Lightning levels.
    Lightning
    Lightning is a subclass of Level, there is only a fixed amount of time for moves to be made.
    Model
    Instantiate a default set of Pieces to use, based on the canonical structure.
    MyTimer  
    Piece
    A Piece is represented as a two dimensional array of null or filled.
    Puzzle
    Puzzle is a subclass of Level, win by removing at least all but two pieces from the bullpen before the move limit is reached.
    Release
    Release is a subclass of Level, win by freeing number sets.
    ReleaseSquare
    The release square takes two more parameters to define the number and color associated with it.
    Square
    Square defines the basic behavior of a square.
    Stars
    Keeps track of how the player performs.
    TestBoard
    Test the functionality of Board and its methods.
    TestCounter
    Validates the counter class runs as should.

    TestLightning  
    TestPiece  
    TestPuzzle  
    TestRelease

    TestStar

    TimerTaskRepeat
